{
    "name": "Olghuth",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Olghuths are amphibious ambush predators that stalk Aucturn\u2019s Undulating Sea. Similar in appearance to a bulbous fish with squat, salamander-like legs and razor-sharp spined fins, olghuths have dozens of eyestalks that line their backs and dense beards of electrified tendrils that can cause temporary paralysis. Olghuths are consumed by constant pain, making them insatiably ravenous. They prefer to eat sapient creatures, and they frequently hunt along coasts, shallows, and ocean trade routes, where they capsize or sink water vehicles.<br/> While many believe olghuths\u2019 hunger causes their pain, centuries\u2011old rumors claim olghuths were once another creature entirely, or perhaps numerous creatures, who mutated into a monstrous amalgam due to Aucturn\u2019s strange energies, which suggests their pain might be due to incompatible biology or mental anguish. Regardless, eating is the only balm for their wounds\u2014after consuming a sapient creature, olghuths become temporarily euphoric and capable of speech. The cryptic, nonsensical ramblings of articulate olghuths are incredibly difficult to parse, but supposedly contain clues to the secrets of existence."
        }
    ],
